---
import ContentSection from '../ContentSection.astro';
import Flowchart from '../Flowchart.astro';

const dofFactors = {
  nodes: [
    { id: "A", label: "Depth of Field Factors" },
    { id: "B", label: "Aperture Size" },
    { id: "C", label: "Focal Length" },
    { id: "D", label: "Subject Distance" },
    { id: "E", label: "Sensor Size" }
  ],
  connections: [
    { from: "A", to: "B" },
    { from: "A", to: "C" },
    { from: "A", to: "D" },
    { from: "A", to: "E" }
  ]
};
---

<ContentSection title="Depth of Field">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Understanding Depth of Field</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Depth of field (DOF) refers to the range of distance in which objects appear acceptably sharp in an image. It's a crucial concept in photography that affects the aesthetic and visual impact of your images.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Key Factors Affecting DOF</h3>
      <Flowchart data={dofFactors} />
      
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Aperture Size (f-stop)</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Larger aperture (smaller f-number) = Shallower DOF</li>
            <li>Smaller aperture (larger f-number) = Greater DOF</li>
            <li>Common uses:
              <ul class="list-circle pl-6 mt-1">
                <li>f/1.4 - f/2.8: Portraits, isolating subjects</li>
                <li>f/8 - f/16: Landscapes, architecture</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Focal Length Impact</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Longer focal lengths create shallower DOF</li>
            <li>Wider angles provide greater DOF</li>
            <li>Affects perspective compression</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Subject Distance</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Closer subjects = Shallower DOF</li>
            <li>Further subjects = Greater DOF</li>
            <li>Critical for macro photography</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ContentSection>